Where {{2308.06374_FO0005||FO}} states that hasChild is the inverse equivalent relation of hasParent, {{2308.06374_FO0006||FO}} states that for each person in the KGs for which we know the parent-child relationship we should know the birth year, and {{2308.06374_FO0007||FO}} states that if {{2308.06374_FO0008||FO}} is a child of {{2308.06374_FO0009||FO}} then {{2308.06374_FO0010||FO}} should be born before {{2308.06374_FO0011||FO}}.
